Remember that INRIA distributes a free CD-ROM containing the whole
Caml distribution and the Caml Web site (including tutorials and
FAQ). The contents of this CD-ROM is available from our WEB server (see
http://pauillac/inria.fr/cdrom/) by you can obtain this CD-ROM for
free: mail to

INRIA - SICS Diffusion
Distribution de Caml Light
B.P. 105
78153 Le Chesnay CEDEX
France 

Don't forget to send an envelope (that can contain a CD-ROM), with
your name and adress, and an International Reply Coupon for stamps
(french people may send 4 french stamps).

Also note that the FAQ is available in the Caml ftp directory as the
file FAQ.tar.gz, the doc is also available in the same directory as
ocaml-3.00-refman.html.tar.gz.
(ftp://ftp.inria.fr/INRIA/lang/caml-light/FAQ.tar.gz
ftp://ftp.inria.fr/INRIA/lang/caml-light/ocaml-3.00-refman.html.tar.gz)

Hope this helps,

Pierre Weis

INRIA, Projet Cristal, Pierre.Weis@inria.fr, http://cristal.inria.fr/~weis/



